<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-06-12T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-06-12T15:00:00-05:00" n="364" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d364">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">811.114 Reidun/155: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Chargé in Norway</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Patterson</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-06-12T16:00:00-04:00">June
                                        12, 1936—4 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>20. Your despatch No. 187, May 27, 1936. The suit and countersuit in
                                the <hi rend="italic">Reidun</hi> case have been dismissed without
                                the payment of money but with a waiver of all claims, if any,
                                against this Government arising out of the detention of the vessel,
                                its officers and crew. Indictments against officers ordered nolle
                                prossed.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>